properties.If_Other_please_specify: Small food store, drinks, canned goods

properties.Additional_notes_or_rds_music_displays: The owner owns a large portion of the back of the store in addition to the storefront, and he uses that space as a place to give free Muay Thai lessons to kids, and a Muay Thai champion (who also teaches over at Costco) comes in to give lessons to kids as well, and the lessons are free in order for the kids to defend themselves. The uncle would also give free water/drinks to the couriers. A lot of people who pass by the uncle's store will say hello to him. If there is a market event in la marqueta, the owner's wife will push her cart over to sell. The owner's children sometimes put their products outside, but the owner himself doesn't like it because he is responsible for the garbage, which is not generated by the owner, but thrown away by passers-by.

properties.Comments: Short wait times, friendly hairstylists, good prices. Very humble, working class clientele, good tunes on the speaker if you like bandas, rancheras, etc. Ok bye

It was cool for a presidents day. But not everyone is down with christian music. Especially for a Monday. Listen don't get me wrong the food was pretty good but not while someone is preaching in tongues catching the spirit.  I seen a lot of that growing up in a community that caught frequencies every so often. Not while having breakfast....allow me to wake up first.......

Great little Mexican place in East Harlem.  The happy hour has drinks discounted (from 4-7pm M-F I believe) and the drinks were very tasty.  We even came back the next night just for drinks.  The food and service was excellent.  The atmosphere was perfect and relaxing.  They do have a ramp over the entrance stairs.  I would highly recommend stopping by after work for some great food and tasty drinks.

properties.Comments: I wanted to try here for a while because the food looked good, and the price looked decent. I was kind of disappointed that they did not serve any alcoholic drinks. When I saw that there were none on the menu, I should have known better. This was kind of big deal for the oth er people I was with,  pretty sure they would have like alcohol. The temperature of the bathroom and where I was sitting was also cold. Overall presentation of my meal was good but had no flavor. The nachos were good.

properties.Store_name: El Barrio Wireless New York Cell Phone Repair Shop

properties.Comments: Absolutely thrilled with my last-minute order! I requested a bouquet of blue roses on very short notice, and this shop  delivered. The bouquet was stunning, fresh, and beautifully arranged with so much care. It made the moment incredibly special. Thank you for going above and beyond! Highly recommend for anyone in need of gorgeous flowers, even in a pinch.

properties.Comments: As a Mexican, this place doesn’t get my stamp of approval. The food gave me a headache (bad quality), lacked flavor, and the enchilada sauce wasn’t strained so I pulled chunks of spices out. The bread was dry and wasn’t even filled all the way. Also, we changed our mind within a couple of minutes of ordering tamales and ordered different entrees that were more expensive. Despite that, they refused to put the tamales back and made us pay. They only take cash.

East Harlem isn't really known for Italian food, and that's why Nocciola is a hidden gem in this neighborhood, and never disappoints. The service is really friendly and attentive. Lily and Antonio are always welcoming. My favorite appetizers are the burrata and the crispy calamari, but you can't go wrong when ordering a pizza. In entrees the chicken parm is a great portion, the carbonara is super creamy, and my friend loves how fluffy the gnocchi is. You have to save room for dessert and order the tiramisu or the panna cotta. Overall a comforting place, friendly service, fresh and affordable food. One of my favorite places in East Harlem.
The service was pretty fast depending on how many people are getting dine in or take out and has a nice atmosphere with some great food
